  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Experimental results are strongly suggesting that PCSK9 and FXR could occur in the
      physiopathology of human joined dyslipidemia. But no data in the literature can validate the
      potential role of these two genes in the lipidic and glucidic metabolism control in
      physiopathological situations. This protocol is based on the hypothesis that the expression
      levels of PCSK 9 and FXR are modified for some patients suffering from insulin resistance and
      dyslipidemia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
